2. Scope of application of the privacy policy

　　(1) Personally identifiable information left by the user while using the application server;
　　(2) Various types of information transmitted by users to other users or non-users through this application server;
　　(3) Various information about other users or non-users that the Application shares with its business partners;
　　(4) Apera Instruments attaches great importance to the protection of user privacy, and has formulated the "Privacy Policy", the user can also through the "Privacy Policy", the user confirms and agrees that the use of its information software to provide services will be deemed to accept the "Privacy Policy".

3. Information disclosure and sharing

　　Ltd. will not willfully disclose, rent or sell the user’s personal information and information to any third party. Except for the following cases:
　　(1) The user himself/herself agrees to share information and data with third parties.
　　(2) To provide certain products and services requested by the user only if the user’s personal information and information are disclosed.
　　(3) Provided at the request of the subjects providing products or services on behalf of this application (unless we notify you otherwise, such subjects do not have the right to use the relevant user’s personal information and information for purposes other than the provision of products and services): Provided in accordance with the requirements of laws, regulations or administrative orders; Provided for the needs of external audits; Users violating the terms of service of the application or the provisions of the use of any other products and services; Provided by the This site assesses that the user’s account is at risk and needs to be protected.
　　(4)To accurately connect within Bluetooth range for device identification, we will collect your device information (including IMEI, Android ID, MEID). 
